HEADWORD: Furry
<hw>Fur"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Fur</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered with fur; dressed in
fur.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Furry</xex> nations.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of fur; <as>as, furry spoils</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resembling fur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

